window.bookSummaryJSON = "In this intensely powerful memoir, America's pre-eminent biographer-historian, who has written so brilliantly about World War II in his acclaimed lives of General Douglas MacArthur ( <i>American Caesar</i>) and Winston Churchill ( <i>The Last Lion</i>), looks back at his own early life. <p> This memoir offers an unrivaled firsthand account of World War II in the Pacific - what it looked like, sounded like, smelled like, and most of all, what it felt like to one who underwent all but the ultimate of its experiences.</p>"; 
